<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><feed xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom" xml:lang="en"><generator uri="https://jekyllrb.com/" version="4.3.3">Jekyll</generator><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/feed.xml" rel="self" type="application/atom+xml"/><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" hreflang="en"/><updated>2025-12-26T14:52:32+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/feed.xml</id><title type="html">blank</title><subtitle></subtitle><entry><title type="html">Pyrenees | Mediterranean Bike trip</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2024/Velo/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Pyrenees | Mediterranean Bike trip"/><published>2024-05-01T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2024-05-01T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2024/Velo</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2024/Velo/"><![CDATA[<p>After defending my PhD, I made a conscious choice and realised an idea that was in my head for many years. Sometimes, life feels overwhelming with screens, notifications, work, and daily stress, especially doing a PhD. So I decided to step away and embrace simplicity : cycling and bivouacking, first by going around the Pyrenees, and then around the Mediterranean sea.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>In April-May, I did a warm-up ride of three weeks starting in Rieumes, the city where I grew up. I pedaled my way through the Pyrenees until the ocean, went to Spain, and all the way to the Mediterranean sea, then heading back to Rieumes. In May, then, I could attend the <a href="https://sfeca2024.sciencesconf.org/">SFECA 2024</a> in Albi and gave a talk there.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_3-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_3-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_3-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_3.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_4-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_4-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_4-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_4.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_5-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_5-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_5-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_5.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_6-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_6-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_6-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_6.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>After that, I set out a longer journey through Corsica, Sardinia, Sicily, and Italy, using trains and boats when my bike wasn’t sufficient, and keeping an intentional slow pace. I spent my days cycling and my nights bivouacking, either alone, with friends, or meeting new people along the way. Traveling by bike is one of my favorite because it allows you to conver good distances (in my case around 2400 km with 27000 of elevation gain), while you have time to enjoy each bout, joyful or challenging.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_7-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_7-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_7-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_7.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_8-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_8-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_8-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_8.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_9-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_9-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_9-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_9.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_10-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_10-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_10-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_10.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <p>This break wasn’t just about exploring new places—it was about recharging my body and mind, having restful sleeps, daily physical activity and time to wander. Sleeping under the stars and focusing on the act of cycling helped me retreat from my last 3 years, take a step back from my life and gain perspectives. I came back in July to enjoy my time with my relatives, refreshed and full of energy, ready for a new chapter.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_11-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_11-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_11-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_11.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_12-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_12-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_12-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_12.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_13-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_13-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_13-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_13.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B6_14-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B6_14-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B6_14-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B6_14.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I took a break after my PhD defense to organise a two-month trip through southern Europe]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Fête de la Science</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2023/Fsci/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Fête de la Science"/><published>2023-10-07T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2023-10-07T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2023/Fsci</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2023/Fsci/"><![CDATA[<p>On October 7th, 2023, I participated in the <a href="https://www.inrae.fr/fete-de-la-science-2023">Fête de la Science</a>. Together with <a href="https://www.instagram.com/clement.gasque/">Clement Gasque</a>, we merged science and art through innovative technology. Here’s how it all came together:</p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B5_3-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B5_3-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B5_3-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B5_3.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B5_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B5_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B5_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B5_2.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <ul> <li> <p>During my PhD, I used a Raspberry Pi device, paired with a camera, to record the behavior of larvae in response to different stimuli.</p> </li> <li> <p>I then employed an algorithm to track the locomotor activity of several individuals.</p> </li> </ul> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/B5_V1.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" autoplay="" controls=""/> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <video src="/assets/video/B5_V2.mp4" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="auto" height="auto" controls=""/> </figure> </div> </div> <ul> <li>When I shared my work-in-progress with Clement, he had the brilliant idea of transforming my data into 3D prints that visualized the behavior of each individual.</li> </ul> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B5_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B5_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B5_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B5_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <ul> <li>We then created unique “postcards” from the 3D models, which we printed live during the event and handed out to the children who attended.</li> </ul> <p>It was a fantastic experience, blending science with creativity in a way that was both fun and engaging!</p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B5_4-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B5_4-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B5_4-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B5_4.png" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I participated in events dedicated to promoting the popularisation of science, engaging with the public to make scientific concepts more accessible and engaging]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Amapola festival</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/Amap/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Amapola festival"/><published>2022-03-20T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-03-20T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/Amap</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/Amap/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 20th of March 2022, I participated to <a href="https://www.amapolafestival.com/">Amapola festival</a> with the artist <a href="http://www.blobsnfluff.com/">Alexia Defluff</a>. We presented a shared project about insects in science.</p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B4_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B4_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B4_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B4_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B4_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B4_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B4_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B4_2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I hosted a stand with Alexia Defluff at Amapola Festival]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Ma Thèse en 180 secondes</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/MT180/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Ma Thèse en 180 secondes"/><published>2022-03-16T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-03-16T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/MT180</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/MT180/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 16th of March 2022, I participated in the regional final of <a href="https://mt180.fr/">MT180</a>. This competition (in French ‘Ma thèse en 180 secondes’) aims to promote public understanding of science at the level of doctoral studies. Participants present their research project to a non-specialist, non-scientific and highly diverse audience. The challenge is to deliver a clear, concise and convincing presentation using simple terms, images and metaphors, all shown on a single slide in just three minutes. You can find the replay <a href="https://www.youtube.com/live/-ahMiMmrvqI?si=sT0TgqMae8bTlHB5&amp;t=5180">here</a>.</p> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B3_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B3_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B3_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B3_2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B3_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B3_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B3_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B3_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I participated in the regional final of MT180]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Talk on the Scientific Method Program, France Culture radio</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/radio/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Talk on the Scientific Method Program, France Culture radio"/><published>2022-03-09T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2022-03-09T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/radio</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2022/radio/"><![CDATA[<p>I presented my PhD research on France Culture’s radio program <a href="https://www.radiofrance.fr/franceculture/podcasts/la-methode-scientifique">The Scientific Method</a>. It was an exciting opportunity to share my work with a broader audience. The replay is available <a href="https://www.radiofrance.fr/franceculture/podcasts/la-methode-scientifique/ecologie-de-la-peur-loup-y-es-tu-5123889">here</a>. My intervention starts at 40 min 18 sec.</p>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[I presented my PhD subject at the radio]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Stand and conference at the Bel Air Festival</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2021/belair/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Stand and conference at the Bel Air Festival"/><published>2021-07-03T14:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2021-07-03T14:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2021/belair</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2021/belair/"><![CDATA[<p>On the 2nd, 3rd and 4th of July 2021, we hosted a stand and gave a public presentation about my master’s project with Dr <a href="https://geode.univ-tlse2.fr/accueil/personnel/sylvie-guillerme">Sylvie Guillerme</a> and Constance Chourau at the <a href="https://belairfestival.fr/souvenirs">Bel Air Festival</a>. This regional event blends music, art and discussions on current issues related to our consumption patterns and biodiversity in the Pyrenees. During the conference, we also presented the results of our first paper <a class="citation" href="#dessart2024color">(Dessart et al., 2024)</a>h.</p> <div class="row mt-3"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B1_1-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B1_1-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B1_1-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B1_1.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B1_2-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B1_2-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B1_2-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B1_2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div> <div class="row"> <div class="col-sm mt-3 mt-md-0"> <figure> <picture> <source class="responsive-img-srcset" srcset="/assets/img/B1_3-480.webp 480w,/assets/img/B1_3-800.webp 800w,/assets/img/B1_3-1400.webp 1400w," sizes="95vw" type="image/webp"/> <img src="/assets/img/B1_3.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded z-depth-1" width="100%" height="auto" loading="eager" onerror="this.onerror=null; $('.responsive-img-srcset').remove();"/> </picture> </figure> </div> </div>]]></content><author><name></name></author><category term="outreach"/><category term="conference"/><summary type="html"><![CDATA[We hosted a stand and gave a public presentation about my master's project]]></summary></entry><entry><title type="html">Martin Dessart</title><link href="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2020/martin-dessart/" rel="alternate" type="text/html" title="Martin Dessart"/><published>2020-05-14T00:00:00+00:00</published><updated>2020-05-14T00:00:00+00:00</updated><id>https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2020/martin-dessart</id><content type="html" xml:base="https://martindessart.github.io/blog/2020/martin-dessart/"><![CDATA[]]></content><author><name></name></author></entry></feed>